value.value: A UTR variant of the 5' UTR.

definition.value: EBI term: 5prime UTR variations - In 5prime UTR (untranslated region).

value.value: A UTR variant of the 3' UTR.

definition.value: EBI term 3prime UTR variations - In 3prime UTR.

value.value: A sequence variant where at least one base of the final codon of an incompletely annotated transcript is changed.

definition.value: EBI term: Partial codon - Located within the final, incomplete codon of a transcript with a shortened coding sequence where the end is unknown.

value.value: A transcript variant occurring within an intron.

definition.value: EBI term: Intronic variations - In intron.

value.value: A sequence variant located in the intergenic region, between genes.

definition.value: EBI term Intergenic variations - More than 5 kb either upstream or downstream of a transcript.

value.value: A sequence variant that changes the first two or last two bases of an intron, or the 5th base from the start of the intron in the orientation of the transcript.

definition.value: EBI term - essential splice site - In the first 2 or the last 2 base pairs of an intron. The 5th base is on the donor (5') side of the intron. Updated to b in line with Cancer Genome Project at the Sanger.

value.value: A sequence variant in which a change has occurred within the region of the splice site, either within 1-3 bases of the exon or 3-8 bases of the intron.

definition.value: EBI term: splice site - 1-3 bps into an exon or 3-8 bps into an intron.

value.value: A sequence variant located 5' of a gene.

definition.value: Different groups annotate up and downstream to different lengths. The subtypes are specific and are backed up with cross references.

value.value: A sequence variant located 3' of a gene.

definition.value: Different groups annotate up and downstream to different lengths. The subtypes are specific and are backed up with cross references.

value.value: A sequence variant located within 5 KB of the end of a gene.

definition.value: EBI term Downstream variations - Within 5 kb downstream of the 3prime end of a transcript.

value.value: A sequence variant located within a half KB of the end of a gene.
A sequence variant located within 5KB 5' of a gene.

definition.value: EBI term Upstream variations - Within 5 kb upstream of the 5prime end of a transcript.

value.value: A sequence variant located within 2KB 5' of a gene.
A gene that encodes for ribosomal RNA.

definition.value: Adjusted heirarchy and names of rRNA_gene terms at the request of Steven Marygold GitHub Issue #513 (https://github.com/The-Sequence-Ontology/SO-Ontologies/issues/513).

value.value: A gene that encodes for an piwi associated RNA.

definition.value: Moved from ncRNA_gene to sncRNA_gene 27 April 2021 to be more consistent with the organization of the ncRNA branch of SO. Requested by FlyBase, moved by Dave Sant. See GitHub Issue #514.

value.value: A gene that encodes an RNase P RNA.

definition.value: Moved under enzymatic_RNA_gene on 18 Nov 2021. See GitHub Issue #533.

value.value: A gene that encodes a RNase_MRP_RNA.

definition.value: Moved under enzymatic_RNA_gene on 18 Nov 2021. See GitHub Issue #533.

value.value: A gene that encodes a long, intervening non-coding RNA.

A mathematically defined repeat (MDR) is a experimental feature that is determined by querying overlapping oligomers of length k against a database of shotgun sequence data and identifying regions in the query sequence that exceed a statistically determined threshold of repetitiveness.

definition.value: Mathematically defined repeat regions are determined without regard to the biological origin of the repetitive region. The repeat units of a MDR are the overlapping oligomers of size k that were used to for the query. Tools that can annotate mathematically defined repeats include Tallymer (Kurtz et al 2008, BMC Genomics: 517) and RePS (Wang et al, Genome Res 12(5): 824-831.).

value.value: A telomerase RNA gene is a non coding RNA gene the RNA product of which is a component of telomerase.
An engineered vector that is able to take part in homologous recombination in a host with the intent of introducing site specific genomic modifications.
A measurable sequence feature that varies within a population.
A genetic marker, discovered using Diversity Arrays Technology (DArT) technology.
A kind of ribosome entry site, specific to Eukaryotic organisms that overlaps part of both 5' UTR and CDS sequence.
A transposon that is disrupted by the insertion of another element.
A repeat that is disrupted by the insertion of another element.
A sequence variant which does not cause a disruption of the translational reading frame.

A transcription factor binding site of variable direct repeats of the sequence PuGGTCA spaced by five nucleotides (DR5) found in the promoters of retinoic acid-responsive genes, to which retinoic acid receptors bind.
A binding site that, in the nucleotide molecule, interacts selectively and non-covalently with polypeptide residues.
A binding site that, in the molecule, interacts selectively and non-covalently with nucleotide residues.

definition.value: See GO:0000166 : nucleotide binding.

value.value: A binding site that, in the molecule, interacts selectively and non-covalently with metal ions.

definition.value: See GO:0046872 : metal ion binding.

value.value: A binding site that, in the molecule, interacts selectively and non-covalently with a small molecule such as a drug, or hormone.
An NTR is a nested repeat of two distinct tandem motifs interspersed with each other.

definition.value: Tracker ID: 3052459.
An element that can exist within the promoter region of a gene.
Mmoved from is_a: SO:0001055 transcriptional_cis_regulatory_region as per request from GREEKC initiative in August 2020.

value.value: An element that only exists within the promoter region of a eukaryotic gene.
A TATA box core promoter of a gene transcribed by RNA polymerase II.
A TATA box core promoter of a gene transcribed by RNA polymerase III.
A core RNA polymerase II promoter element with consensus (G/A)T(T/G/A)(T/A)(G/T)(T/G)(T/G).
A discontinuous core element of RNA polymerase II transcribed genes, situated downstream of the TSS. It is composed of three sub elements: SI, SII and SIII.
A sub element of the DCE core promoter element, with consensus sequence CTTC.
A sub element of the DCE core promoter element with consensus sequence CTGT.
A sub element of the DCE core promoter element with consensus sequence AGC.

DNA segment that ranges from about -250 to -40 relative to +1 of RNA transcription start site, where sequence specific DNA-binding transcription factors binds, such as Sp1, CTF (CCAAT-binding transcription factor), and CBF (CCAAT-box binding factor).
The minimal portion of the promoter required to properly initiate transcription in RNA polymerase II transcribed genes.

definition.value: A regulatory promoter element that is distal from the TSS.
A DNA sequence to which bacterial RNA polymerase sigma 70 binds, to begin transcription.
A DNA sequence to which bacterial RNA polymerase sigma 54 binds, to begin transcription.

value.value: A conserved region about 12-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units, involved with sigma factor 54.
A conserved region about 24-bp upstream of the start point of bacterial transcription units, involved with sigma factor 54.
An A box within an RNA polymerase III type 1 promoter.

definition.value: The A box can be found in the promoters of type 1 and type 2 (pol III) so sub-typing here allows the part of relationship of the subtypes to remain true.
